<br>
This is a good soloing spot as often even if there is a group at camp 2 they won't be pulling all the way back to the alcove.  The only thing you need to remember is you absolutely can't let them run away, because they will aggro the guys in the tents when they run.  So, keep them rooted!<br>
<br>
You can also single pull Ringo, he doesn't have any interesting loot but he's experience while you're waiting for the bandits to respawn.  Pull him up to the small ledge just above where he sits, and keep him rooted there.  Again, groups at camp 2 often don't bother with Ringo.<br>
<br>
Once you get to 25 or so you should be able to camp a spire in East Karana outside Splitpaw (head due south from the North Karana zone); the gnolls there drop fine steel weapons, and the stacks of rainwater add up after a while.  You can often find pick-up groups heading inside also.<br>
<br>
Solusek's Eye, Sol A, is also a good place although as a, er, ogre-sized gnome you are going to have to keep yourself shrunk in order to get through the window room.  Keep these guys rooted too, they do bring friends!  You can either pull to the entrance or if you go down the stairs and through the window room, head right and down, there is a small room there that's good to pull to.  It's right near a zone to Sol B (marked C on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/solusekseyemap.html"><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">this map</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->) so you can run to the zone if you have problems.  The goblins drop poison ingredients that sell well, also occasionally weapons, if I recall correctly.<br>
<br>
When you reach your early 30s, go to the Eastern Wastes and head along the north shoreline, the ulthorks here are excellent experience and money.  Look for the ulthork hunters rather than the warriors, they are much easier kills.  Ulthorks drop armour, also velium weapons and occasional random other things.  The walrus tooth is a good piercing weapon, and save any ulthork tusks you get as you can turn these in 4 at a time for a quest that will return you a random high-price gem (I got a blue diamond the first time, black sapphire the second).  I spent a lot of time here!  Pulling to just west of the coldain huts (marked 3 on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/velious/easternwastesmap.html"><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">this map</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->) is safe, the ulthorks don't wander over that far - guess they don't like the dwarf smell.<br>
<br>
You might also consider going to the outcast bandit camp in Echo Caverns (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/luclin/echocavernsmap.html"><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">area 7</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->), in your early to mid 30s.  Almost all the named drop a special item that will sell to merchants for 3-7pp (run down to the evil city just down the hall to get good prices).  Crinthia also sometimes drops a ring that would be excellent for a young shaman to wear.  The normal &quot;outcast mutants&quot; generally don't drop anything.  It would be safest with a friend while you are younger but well worth investigating.<br>
<br>
You could also try the mountain giant fortress in <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqatlas.com/kunark/frontiermtnsmap.html"><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Frontier Mountains</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, there are often pick-up groups around here, the loot is good, and the experience is good up to about 34.  It's a little dangerous to get there however, you will have to be alert for wandering giants.  There is, of course, safe hunting to be had in the Overthere, but it is not very good money on the whole, so you might prefer other locations.<br>
<br>
Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chasefv>ChaseFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#339933><b>Keeper of the Trades' Scrolls</b></font></span><br>  Posts: 383<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/29/03 6:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1860.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where should I hunt?</span><hr size=1> If you seek an out of the way place, you might try the kobold camps just into Stonebrunt mountains from the Warrens. There are two kobolds right outside the entrance to the Warrens who can be pulled one at a time, there are wanderers, and there are several camps. The further away from the entrance you go, the more careful you need to be about wanderers. Know the shortest way to the exit, and keep Spirit of Wolf cast upon yourself at all times. Other than the odd adventurer passing through to reach the Gulf of Gunthak, or the occassional ranger or druid coming to help control the animal population, there will be few others present.<br>
<br>
The kobolds drop some lovely brass weaponry, a little cash, various armors, various research components, some quest items, and best of all: kobold meat! Kobold meat, in the hands of even the most junior chef, can be prepared to make some truly delicious steaks. If you are able to move carefully and quickly, you can sell your trophies at the kerran village in the center of the zone, but it will be very dangerous to get to. You might have an easier time running down to the docks and sneaking into the Gulf of Gunthak and selling at the Lighthouse.<br>
<br>
The trick to this though, is getting *through* the Warrens to these camps. At 25, running through the king's room is a chancy stroll. If you are able to find transportation directly to Stonebrunt, you'd have an easier time of things. <br>
<br>
Another thing to watch out for is the wandering animals, as they will attack anyone, and some will be much stronger than a young gnome like yourself. This is a very rewarding place to hunt, but if and only if you are very, very careful.<br>
<br>
Hunt well and safely, young gnome. I hope you find your mommy. *sniff*<br>
